Renders `TypedEntry`s into a Plover dictionary under the "smart" profile, where the editor's auto-close, type-over, and block-expand behavior is trusted to supply matching brackets/quotes automatically — so only the keystrokes the editor won't already produce are emitted. This is the thinnest of the render profiles: both functions are one-line wrappers around the shared machinery in `render/mod.rs` (`wrap`, `build_dict`, `entry_events`), differing from sibling profiles only in the `SMART` editor-behavior constant passed to `entry_events`.

`render_smart(entry: &TypedEntry) -> Result<(String, String), RenderError>` produces a single Plover `(key, value)` pair for one entry; `build_smart_dict(entries: &[TypedEntry]) -> Result<BuildResult, RenderError>` maps that over a whole entry set into a `BuildResult`. Errors surface from `entry_events`/`wrap` when a template has an unresolved chunk or movement compilation fails — this file adds no validation of its own.

Coupled to `crate::editor::SMART`, which encodes what the target editor auto-handles (closing brackets, type-over, block expansion); if that constant's semantics change, the keystrokes this profile omits will drift out of sync with what the editor actually does. Also depends on `super::{BuildResult, build_dict, entry_events, wrap}` from `render/mod.rs` — those are the real logic; this file is just profile selection.